docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, April 29 (AP) -- Tomorrow is the first deadline for something like a million new tax collectors -- the householders who pay a domestic helper an average of $4 a week or more. The new Social Security law that went into effect Jan. 1 qualified domestic help for Social Security if they made $50 a quarter or more from any one employer.

headline.main: Million New Tax Collectors Face Social Security Deadline Today

docs.abstract: Some 1 million householders to make 1st tax payments to Internal Revenue Service for domestics earning $50 or more, 1st qr; law provisions revd
